def: The act of detecting; the laying open what was concealed orhidden; discovery; as, the detection of a thief; the detection offraud, forgery, or a plot.Such secrets of guilt are never from detection. D. Webster.
Given to melancholy; depressed; melancholy; dejected; unhappy.Just as the melancholic eye Sees fleets and armies in the sky. Prior.
A hydrocarbon radical regarded as an essential residue ofpropine and allied compounds.
A disease in horses and swine, in which the upper part of thethroat, or groups of lymphatic glands elsewhere, swells.
A device for pulling off boots.
The aggregate value of the different stocks in which a loan togovernment is now usually funded. M'Culloch.
To revoke or annul, as a promise. Chapman.
